---
title: 'Repository List'
description: >
  This page lists known third-party repositories available
  for ReaPack, the package manager for REAPER.
types:
  script:       'script'
  effect:       'effect'
  theme:        'theme'
  extension:    'extension'
  langpack:     'language pack'
  webinterface: 'web interface'
  other:        'misc package'
---

p
  ' This page lists known free third-party ReaPack repositories.


ul.table
  li: ul.help
    li: a href="https://github.com/cfillion/reapack/wiki#import-a-repository"
      i.fa.fa-info-circle
      | How to import a repository?
    li: a href="https://github.com/cfillion/reapack.com/edit/master/config/repos.yml"
      i.fa.fa-pencil
      | Edit this list
    li
      a.copyAll> href="javascript:;"
        i.fa.fa-copy
        | Copy all
      span.copied.hidden
        | (Copied!)

  - data.repos.each do |repo|
    li
      .left.icon
        - if repo[:default]
          i.fa.fa-asterisk title="Included in the default configuration"
        - elsif repo[:featured]
          i.fa.fa-star title="Featured"
        - else
          .hidden &nbsp;

      .left
        a href=repo[:link] = repo[:name][0...24]
        br
        .desc
          - if repo[:packages].empty?
            | This repository is empty
          - else
            = repo[:packages].sort_by {|t, c| [-c, t] }.map {|type, count| \
              pluralize number_with_delimiter(count),
                current_page.data.types[type.to_sym] \
            }.join ', '

      a.index href=repo[:index]
        code #{repo[:index]}

h2#upload Share your content

div.contribute
  p#pr: img src="/images/pull_request.png" alt="Creating a Pull Request on GitHub"
  p ReaPack is a powerful tool for distributing REAPER resources.
    The <a href="https://github.com/ReaTeam">ReaTeam</a> repositories hosted
    on GitHub are the preferred method for sharing community resources.

  p Documentation for building your own repository is available on the
    <a href="https://github.com/cfillion/reapack/wiki/Index-Format">wiki</a>.
    Check out the <a href="https://github.com/cfillion/reapack-index/wiki">reapack-index</a>
    project if you use git as your version control system.

  p Come discuss in the <a href="http://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=169127">development thread</a>
    on the REAPER forum!

- content_for :javascripts do
  == javascript_include_tag 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/clipboard.js/1.5.13/clipboard.min.js', defer: true
  == javascript_include_tag 'repos', defer: true
